
@startuml

' Define classes and relationships based on the system requirement

class House {
  - address: String
  - buildingMaterial: BuildingMaterial (wood, brick, concrete)
  + getBasement(): Basement
}

class Basement {
  - name: String
  - size: int
}

class EarthBasement extends Basement {
  - humidityLevel: double
}

class ConcreteBasement extends Basement {}

class SemiDetachedHouse extends House {
  - hasOwnGarden: boolean
  - numberOfWindows: int
  - parkingFacility: ParkingFacility (carports or garage)
}

interface ParkingFacility {}

class Carports implements ParkingFacility {
  - isDouble: boolean
  - hasFlatRoof: boolean
}

class Garage implements ParkingFacility {
  - hasAutomaticDoor: boolean
}

class Company {
  - name: String
  - address: String
}

class JobLog {
  - hoursWorked: int
  - agreedPrice: double
  - company: Company
  - house: House
}

' Relationships

House "1" -- "0..1" Basement : has
SemiDetachedHouse "1" -- "1" ParkingFacility : has
ParkingFacility <|-- Carports
ParkingFacility <|-- Garage
House "1" -- "1..*" Company : serviced by
Company "1" -- "0..*" JobLog : has
House "1" -- "0..*" JobLog : logged in

enum BuildingMaterial {
  wood
  brick
  concrete
}

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **`House`**: Base class with common attributes like `address` and `buildingMaterial`.
- **`Basement`**: Abstract base class extended into two types:
  - `EarthBasement`: Has additional attribute `humidityLevel`.
  - `ConcreteBasement`: No extra fields.
- **`SemiDetachedHouse`**: Specialized house type with additional fields like `hasOwnGarden`, `numberOfWindows`, and a choice between `Carports` or `Garage`.
- **`Carports` and `Garage`**: Implement the `ParkingFacility` interface to represent the two possible parking options.
- **`Company` and `JobLog`**: A many-to-many relationship is represented via `JobLog`, storing details of jobs done at each house.

